Hello Gio,

Following is the roadmap highlighted on the steps that needs to be
performed, take some time to check how to initiate this project as well
some research on the tools that could be used to perform it.

Build a Python script that:

   1.

   Connects to an IMAP mailbox and downloads messages as .eml
   2.

   Parses headers + authentication results (SPF/DKIM/DMARC)
   3.

   Extracts sender domain, checks reputation signals (AbuseIPDB + DNSBLs),
   and domain age (WHOIS)
   4.

   Sends email content to a *local* LLM for intent analysis
   (phishing/bec/benign/etc.)
   5.

   Produces a structured report per email that explains authenticity +
   likely intent + spoofing/fraud risk

--
Regards,

